messages.message: Good afternoon, I've been getting a danger/PR warning for my PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/30208) that says "Cannot find a merge base between danger_base and danger_head. If you are using shallow clone/fetch, try increasing the --depth" and I was wondering if anyone's run into this/knows what's causing it (some threads say it has to do with number of commits?). Thank you!
I think this means you should squash commits but @shiqi told me that for the time being danger is ignoreable

> either your branch has > 10 diverged commits and need squash, or you need to rebase master
> 
>  but danger check is ignorable currently
ooh, thats v helpful, thank you!
